<item>
            <title>[LU-13903] Make &quot;configure --disable-modules&quot; more useful</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13903</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When configuring with --disable-modules some things don&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&#160; Some configure tests for glibc support are included in &quot;LC_PROG_LINUX&quot; which is not run when --disable-modules is selected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&#160; Some tools need include files from {lustre,lnet}/include/uapi but these are not available with --disable-modules&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&#160; test_410 fails if kinode.ko wasn&apos;t build, but this is not built with --disable-modules&lt;/p&gt;</description>
